SUMMARY:Seattle: Hitt's Hill
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Hitt’s Hill Park . \nJoin EarthCorps and Green Seattle Partnership to restore Hitt’s Hill! Events consist mostly of removing non-native species (like ivy and blackberry) and preparing areas for our winter planting events. No experience necessary! \nPlease note: We are no longer able to provide port-o-potties (portable bathrooms) to events at this location. Please visit Rainier Playfield\, 3700 S Alaska St\, Seattle\, WA 98118 for a restroom\, or a local grocery store\, like PCC. \nThe Basics \nRegistration is required. EarthCorps supplies gloves\, tools\, water and snack bars. We will teach you everything you need to know! No experience necessary\, just come ready to learn something new! Be sure to sign in at registration when you arrive. \nRegister to meet.
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/seattle-hitts-hill/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/home-NEW-2-Catherine-Anstett-Trolls-Knoll-gloves.jpg
END:VEVENT
