SUMMARY:International Day of Forests at Westcrest Park
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Westcrest Park. \nJoin Dirt Corps this March to celebrate the International Day of Forests and help us care for this section of the West Duwamish Greenbelt. We’ll be learning about this international celebration and forest care event and the tree species present in Westcrest Park. We’ll then be caring for our restoration area by applying mulch around the native plants and trees and removing weeds (looking at you blackberry!). We hope to see you there! \nRegister
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/international-day-of-forests-at-westcrest-park/
LOCATION:Westcrest Park\, 9000 8th Avenue SW\, Seattle\, WA\, 98106
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/home-new-2-catherine-anstett-trolls-knoll-gloves.jpg
